Title: Quantum Stabilization of Compactified AdS_5

Authors: Walter D. Goldberger and Ira Z. Rothstein

Comments: 11 pages, Latex; a^4log(a) dependence no longer present, revised

discussion and conclusionsJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B491 (2000) 339-344

We investigate the role of quantum fluctuations in the system composed of twobranes bounding a region of AdS. It is shown that the modulus effectivepotential generated by quantum fluctuations of both brane and bulk fields isincapable of stabilizing the space naturally at the separation needed togenerate the hierarchy. Consequently, a classical stabilization mechanism isrequired. We describe the proper method of regulating the loop integrals andshow that, for large brane separation, the quantum effects are power suppressedand therefore have negligible affects on the bulk dynamics once a classicalstabilization mechanism is in place.